FBIS3-26366 "drchi025_o_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Jiangsu Secretary Promotes Joint Stock System OW0702024194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0232 GMT 7 Feb 94 OW0702024194 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Nanjing, February 7 (XINHUA) -- The Yizheng Chemical Fiber Corporation will become the first enterprise from the mainland to go public in Hong Kong this year, according to an official in this capital of Jiangsu Province. He said more and more enterprises in this, China's most advanced industrial province are employing the share-holding system and have separated their property ownership from their management. According to statistics, more than 100 enterprises in Jiangsu have raised funds by issuing stocks, 600 practise the liabilities limited system and about 10,000 have implemented the partnership system. Jiangsu has about 1,000 large and medium-sized enterprises, and more than 100,000 rural industrial enterprises. With the encouragement of the provincial government, many enterprises have become corporations in order to compete on the market since the beginning of the 1990s. In addition, the provincial government has introduced the joint stock system to transportation departments and enterprises involved in basic and high-tech industries, as well as foreign trade organizations and rural industrial enterprises. According to Chen Huanyou, governor of the province, Jiangsu will further expand the system this year.
